# SDD Control Catalog

This catalog defines executable guardrail controls for Spec-Driven Development.

| Control ID | Normative Control | Applies In Phase(s) | Validation Command | Evidence Artifact(s) | Owner | Gate |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| SDD-C-001 | Work items MUST remain blocked with BLOCKED_MISSING_INPUTS when required business or non-functional inputs are unresolved. | Discover, Specify | make quality-sdd-check | specs/<work-item>/spec.md | Product + Architecture | fail |
| SDD-C-002 | Implementation MUST NOT start until SPEC_READY=true and all readiness counters/sign-offs satisfy the gate. | Plan, Implement | make quality-sdd-check | specs/<work-item>/spec.md, specs/<work-item>/tasks.md | Architecture | fail |
| SDD-C-003 | Implementation-ready specs MUST reference an approved ADR through ADR path and ADR status. | High-Level Architecture, Specify | make quality-sdd-check | specs/<work-item>/spec.md, docs/**/architecture/decisions/*.md | Architecture | fail |
| SDD-C-004 | Normative requirements MUST use deterministic wording (MUST, MUST NOT, SHALL, EXACTLY ONE OF) and MUST NOT use ambiguous terms. | Specify | make quality-sdd-check | specs/<work-item>/spec.md | Architecture | fail |
| SDD-C-005 | Each work item MUST define applicable SDD-C-### controls in the normative controls section. | Specify, Plan | make quality-sdd-check | specs/<work-item>/spec.md | Architecture | fail |
| SDD-C-006 | Each work item MUST declare the implementation stack profile and agent execution model before code changes begin. | High-Level Architecture, Specify | make quality-sdd-check | specs/<work-item>/spec.md | Architecture | fail |
| SDD-C-007 | Architecture and implementation slices MUST preserve Clean Architecture dependency direction and DDD bounded contexts. | High-Level Architecture, Implement | make infra-validate | specs/<work-item>/architecture.md, implementation diff | Architecture | fail |
| SDD-C-008 | Shift-left testing MUST prioritize the lowest valid layer and keep pyramid ratios aligned with governance policy. | Plan, Verify | make quality-test-pyramid | specs/<work-item>/traceability.md, test outputs | Engineering | fail |
| SDD-C-009 | Security controls MUST be explicit for authn/authz, secret handling, and least privilege in normative requirements. | Discover, Specify | make quality-sdd-check | specs/<work-item>/spec.md | Security | fail |
| SDD-C-010 | Observability controls MUST define logs, metrics, traces, and diagnostics ownership for operated paths. | Specify, Operate | make quality-sdd-check | specs/<work-item>/spec.md, specs/<work-item>/traceability.md | Operations | fail |
| SDD-C-011 | Documentation MUST be updated in the Document phase for both blueprint and consumer perspectives when behavior/contracts change. | Document | make docs-build && make docs-smoke | docs/blueprint/**, docs/platform/** | Documentation + Operations | fail |
| SDD-C-012 | Deterministic validation evidence MUST be captured in traceability before completion of the work item. | Verify, Operate | make quality-hooks-run | specs/<work-item>/traceability.md | Engineering | fail |
| SDD-C-013 | Runtime capability specs targeting stackit-* profiles MUST prefer STACKIT managed services by default; any non-managed alternative MUST include explicit approved exception rationale. | Discover, Specify, High-Level Architecture | make quality-sdd-check | specs/<work-item>/spec.md, specs/<work-item>/architecture.md, AGENTS.decisions.md | Architecture + Operations | fail |
| SDD-C-014 | Work-item specs MUST declare the local-first runtime baseline (Docker Desktop Kubernetes context policy, Crossplane/Helm provisioning, ESO+Argo+Keycloak runtime identity) or record an explicit approved exception rationale. | Discover, High-Level Architecture, Specify | make quality-sdd-check | specs/<work-item>/spec.md, specs/<work-item>/architecture.md, AGENTS.decisions.md | Architecture + Operations | fail |
| SDD-C-015 | Plan and task artifacts MUST include the app onboarding minimum Make-target contract, including canonical port-forward wrappers, whenever implementation scope can affect app delivery workflows. | Plan, Implement, Document, Operate | make quality-sdd-check | specs/<work-item>/plan.md, specs/<work-item>/tasks.md, docs/platform/consumer/app_onboarding.md | Architecture + Platform Engineering | fail |
| SDD-C-016 | Publish phase MUST include a deterministic PR context artifact (`pr_context.md`) with requirement coverage, key reviewer files, validation evidence, risk/rollback, and deferred proposals. | Publish | make quality-sdd-check | specs/<work-item>/pr_context.md, .github/pull_request_template.md | Architecture + Engineering | fail |
| SDD-C-017 | Before publish, repository-wide hardening review MUST be completed and recorded in `hardening_review.md` with findings fixed, observability/diagnostics changes, architecture/code-quality compliance, and proposals-only section. | Verify, Operate, Publish | make quality-hardening-review | specs/<work-item>/hardening_review.md | Architecture + Operations | fail |
| SDD-C-018 | Consumer work that applies a temporary workaround for a blueprint-managed defect MUST include upstream escalation lifecycle fields (issue URL, workaround path, replacement trigger, review date) until upstream fix is adopted. | Specify, Plan, Operate, Publish | make quality-sdd-check | specs/<work-item>/spec.md, .github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/bug_report.yml | Platform Engineering + Operations | fail |
| SDD-C-019 | Specs MUST use explicit `[NEEDS CLARIFICATION]` markers for unresolved inputs and MUST clear them (`Open clarification markers count = 0`) before `SPEC_READY=true`. | Discover, High-Level Architecture, Specify, Plan | make quality-sdd-check | specs/<work-item>/spec.md | Product + Architecture | fail |
| SDD-C-020 | Code-assistant execution MUST follow the full SDD lifecycle by default; any SDD bypass MUST be an explicit user opt-out instruction captured in work-item context. | Discover, High-Level Architecture, Specify, Plan, Implement, Verify, Document, Operate, Publish | make quality-sdd-check | AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md, specs/<work-item>/context_pack.md | Product + Architecture | fail |
| SDD-C-021 | Starting a new SDD work item via canonical scaffold tooling MUST create and checkout a dedicated non-default branch unless an explicit opt-out flag is provided. | Discover, Plan | make quality-sdd-check | blueprint/contract.yaml, scripts/bin/blueprint/spec_scaffold.py, make/blueprint.generated.mk | Architecture + Engineering | fail |
| SDD-C-022 | For work touching HTTP route handlers, query/filter logic, or new API endpoints, plan and publish artifacts MUST include a local smoke gate with positive-path curl assertions and explicit pr_context.md evidence (`Endpoint \| Method \| Auth \| Result`). | Plan, Verify, Publish | make quality-sdd-check | specs/<work-item>/plan.md, specs/<work-item>/pr_context.md, specs/<work-item>/traceability.md | Architecture + Operations | fail |
| SDD-C-023 | For filter or payload-transform logic, test planning and implementation MUST include at least one positive-path unit assertion with matching fixture/request values and preserved output fields; empty-result-only assertions MUST NOT satisfy this gate. | Plan, Implement, Verify | make quality-sdd-check | specs/<work-item>/plan.md, specs/<work-item>/tasks.md, specs/<work-item>/traceability.md | Architecture + Engineering | fail |
| SDD-C-024 | Any reproducible pre-PR smoke/curl/deterministic-check finding MUST be translated into a failing automated regression test first and turned green with the implementation fix in the same work item; deterministic exceptions MUST be explicitly documented in publish artifacts. | Plan, Implement, Verify, Publish | make quality-sdd-check | specs/<work-item>/plan.md, specs/<work-item>/tasks.md, specs/<work-item>/traceability.md, specs/<work-item>/hardening_review.md | Architecture + Engineering | fail |
